sentences: Joe Copcutt (born 2 August 1988 from London, England) is an English metal bassist.
Copcutt's musical career began when he joined 12 Ton Method in 2006 around the time of leaving the band in 2008 he joined Rise to Remain replacing Theo Tan.

Copcutt left Rise to Remain in 2012 along with Pat Lundy.
In 2013 Copcutt formed a new London based band named Zoax with Adam Carroll, Dan Prasad, Doug Wotherspoon & Jon Rogers.
In 2018 he joined Carroll in the newly formed The Gore Club.
In that same year he joined AxeWound.
